        <p>I counted everything. I counted the steps to the road, the steps up to church, the number of dishes and silverware I washed… anything that could be counted, I did.</p>
      </blockquote>
      <div class="marcus-cite">— Katherine Johnson, interview with NASA, 2015</div>
      <div class="bridge">
        This is Tenet X — <strong>Memento Mori — Remember That You Will Die.</strong> Johnson lived to 101. She spent every day counting, calculating, building. She didn't waste a single one. While the world told her she couldn't, she quietly proved them wrong with math they couldn't argue with. A Grithosian doesn't waste days. Every one of them is numbered — and Johnson used every single one.
      </div>
